<br>
I'm sure VI would want to kick this one around internally for a long while to wrinkle out any irons.  If you have an established relationship with a GM or a developer, initiating the discussion there would be best.  If you can sell the idea to someone that roams the halls in VI, it's much more likely to at least be discussed seriously by the developers.  If not, there's feedback and the developer's board.  Championing a change is slow and very frustrating, even when there are many others from other servers also pushing for the change. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ueliezeroferudin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Eliezer of Erudin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 283<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/28/02 12:10:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1206.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: That one is really hard</span><hr size=1> The main problem that makes VI very hesitant about allowing a Religion switch is the fact that Religion is so very tied into Faction.<br>
<br>
Take this example of a potential abuse:  Take a Rallos worshipping Half-Elf Bard.  They play for awhile, maybe even go to the Plane of Growth and take some hefty Tunare based faction hits.  Then he has a change of heart and switches to Tunare worship?  What happens to his faction?<br>
<br>
From VI's statements I have a feeling that they were a bit sloppy in programming Religion/Faction and making adjustments to one might seriously screw up the other. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ucylria.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Cylria</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 22<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/28/02 4:02:11 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1206.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: That one is really hard</span><hr size=1> The simplist solution would be to make changing religeon be part of a quest. The quest (it can be long or simple) would require amiable or higher faction with the church you are switching to. This wouldn't require much code changes since most quests require your faction to be at a certain level.<br>
